Package InfrastructureManager.ModuleManagement

Class ModuleConnector

java.lang.Object
InfrastructureManager.ModuleManagement.ModuleConnector
public class ModuleConnector
extends java.lang.Object
Class that is in charge of connecting PlatformModule objects, based on connection raw data. In a more concrete manner, creates Connection objects based on the raw data and adds them to each PlatformModule. It does so by searching for the module where the connection's input is provided and adding a connection related to that input in said module.

  • Method Details

    • connectModule

      public void connectModule​(PlatformModule module) throws IncorrectIONameException, ModuleNotDefinedException, IncorrectInputException
      Adds connection to a module based on its inputs. For each input, all of the defined connections in the raw data will be created and passed to the module.
      Parameters:
      module - Module to connect
      Throws:
      IncorrectIONameException - If in the raw data, the input or output in a connection was defined with a wrong naming convention.
      ModuleNotDefinedException - If a raw connection is defined using a module whose name does not correspond to one of the existing modules.
      IncorrectInputException - If a raw connection is defined using an input name that does not correspond to the predefined input names of this module.
